text.tspan: The quick toggle allows people to quickly figure out it's a firewall issue
without having to dive into firewall rules.
If someone wishes to use an alternate firewall, it's also nice to not have
to jump into another page to turn off firewalld.
Restricting to just one line of information is to allow the firewall reside
at the top of the networking page (without getting in the way) and it
provides a simple clickable target to edit the firewall.
As the network can all be configured correctly, yet nothing might work
due to the firewall, it makes sense to add the toggle and summary at
Firewall on the Networking Page — November 2017
